comments: The course should follow the interactive web-based approach that MATH 115 uses. It is SO MUCH BETTER. Teaching wise this course is stuck in the 20th century when compared to 115 and this makes the learning experience for those who came from 115 way harder.

narratives.question_text: Would you recommend this course to another student? Please explain.
comments: I do not recommend taking MATH 120 unless you really have to for your major. There are other ways to learn multivariable calculus that won't bring you so much despair when compared to this. Honestly Kahn Academy would compare equally.
I would only recommend this course if it was needed for a major.
